The paper discusses the use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) as a tool for knowledge representation and reasoning (KRR) in AI, which suggests that cs.AI is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for proper development tools and interoperability mechanisms, which suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of ASP for educational purposes, which suggests that cs.EDU is a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the high expressiveness of ASP, which suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are also possible sub-categories.
